<p style="text-align: left;">
 
<span style="font-size: 25px;"><strong>1906-06-21 &#8211; The Loveland Register &#8211; First Advertisement For Idlewild</strong></span>




<br>
<br>
<span style="font-size: 20px;"><i><strong>Transcription</strong></i></span> 



<br>
<i>"When you want to spend a day of rest and quiet got to Iydlwilde. Fishing is better here than any place on the Thompson. Iydlewilde is perfectly situated for an ideal summer resort. Tents are rented by the day, week or season at very reasonable rates. Meals furnished if desired. For full information and reservation, write Mrs. Ella VanBramer, Prop. Drake, Colorado"</i>


<br><br>
<span style="font-size: 20px;"><i><strong>People</strong></i></span> 
<br>




<a href='https://www.idlewildlodge.org/posts/ella-van-bramer/'>Ella Van Bramer</a>




<br>



<br>
<span style="font-size: 20px;"><i><strong>Details</strong></i></span> 


<br>
<i>Date: 1906-06-21</i>


<br>
<i>Location: USA, Colorado, Loveland</i>





<br>
<i>Source: The Loveland Register [USA, Colorado, Loveland], 1906-06-21</i>
<br>


<i>Permalink:</i>
<a href="https://www.idlewildlodge.org/article/1906-06-21-the-loveland-register-first-advertisement-for-idlewild/">https://www.idlewildlodge.org/article/1906-06-21-the-loveland-register-first-advertisement-for-idlewild/</a>
</p>
