<p style="text-align: left;">
 
<span style="font-size: 25px;"><strong>1906-06-14 &#8211; Loveland Register &#8211; Ella Van Bramer Names Idlewild</strong></span>




<br>
<br>
<span style="font-size: 20px;"><i><strong>Transcription</strong></i></span> 



<br>
<i>"Mrs. Ella Van Bramer has named her colony of tents in the hills, Eydl-wilde. It is located just beyond the second canon, about three miles this side of the Forks. Mrs. Van Bramer is fixing it up in rather artistic style and it will be vastly popular with the Loveland folk during the summer."</i>


<br><br>
